cs.SE, cs.PL, cs.LO, cs.SD, cs.OH

Reasoning: 
- cs.SE (Software Engineering) is the most likely category as the paper investigates the use of contracts in software development practice. 
- cs.PL (Programming Languages) is also likely as contracts are a language feature in Eiffel, C#, and Java. 
- cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) is relevant as contracts are a form of lightweight formal specification. 
- cs.SD (Soundness and Completeness) is relevant as contracts help maintain consistency between specification and implementation. 
- cs.OH (Other Computer Science) is a possibility as the paper covers a broad range of topics related to contracts in software development.
